---
import { getEntry } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const page = await getEntry('pages', 'home');

const title = page?.data.title ?? "intellectsalt.com — The Essential Seasoning of the Mind";
const description = page?.data.description ?? "Premium brandable domain available for strategic acquisition.";
const image = page?.data.image;
const publishedDate = page?.data.publishedDate;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  image={image}
  canonicalURL="https://intellectsalt.com/"
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section
    class="relative overflow-hidden min-h-[70vh] flex items-center"
    style="background-image: url('https://imagedelivery.net/-sPAUAWeA405NiWJ0SNIQA/14c447b1-fc32-41d5-a132-d9ce1f610e00/public'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;"
  >
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-950/70 backdrop-blur-[2px]"></div>
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-20 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-24 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-accent-light font-medium text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
          Premium Brandable Domain
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-serif font-bold text-brand-50 mb-6 leading-tight">
          intellectsalt<span class="text-accent">.</span>com
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-300 font-serif italic mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          The Essential Seasoning of the Mind
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-400 text-lg mb-10 max-w-2xl">
          Available for Strategic Acquisition
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:sales@desertrich.com?subject=intellectsalt.com%20Acquisition%20Inquiry"
          class="cta-button text-lg"
        >
          Inquire About Acquisition →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 prose-custom">
    <!-- The Concept -->
    <h2>The Concept</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Intellect</strong> is the mind&rsquo;s capacity for rational thought, understanding,
      and the acquisition of knowledge &mdash; the faculty that enables logical reasoning,
      discrimination, and the comprehension of complex ideas.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Salt</strong> (sodium chloride, NaCl) is the foundational compound formed from acid
      and base, renowned as a seasoning, preservative, and essential participant in biological
      processes &mdash; including the precise ionic balance required for life itself.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Intellect Salt</strong> fuses these two elemental forces into a single, unforgettable
      name. It evokes the <em>seasoning</em> that makes thought vivid and memorable, the
      <em>preservative</em> that safeguards wisdom across generations, and the
      <em>biochemical foundation</em> that makes sharp cognition possible in the first place.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- Philosophical Depth -->
    <h2>Philosophical Depth</h2>
    <p>
      Ralph Waldo Emerson, in his essay <em>Intellect</em>, captured the transcendent power of
      the mind:
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      &ldquo;Water dissolves wood, and iron, and salt; air dissolves water; electric fire
      dissolves air, but the intellect dissolves fire, gravity, laws, method, and the subtlest
      unnamed relations of nature in its resistless menstruum.&rdquo;
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Here, intellect is portrayed as the ultimate solvent &mdash; capable of transcending even
      physical laws through pure thought. <strong>Intellect Salt</strong> grounds this lofty
      philosophical power in the tangible, essential element that makes such thought biologically
      and culturally sustainable.
    </p>
    <p>
      Historically, &ldquo;salt&rdquo; has also signified refined wit and intellectual liveliness
      (&ldquo;Attic salt&rdquo;). The name therefore operates on multiple resonant levels:
      chemistry, philosophy, culture, and the sharp edge of human intelligence.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- The Science -->
    <h2>The Science: Brain Chemistry &amp; the Cultivation of Intellect</h2>
    <p>
      Intellect is not an abstract gift alone &mdash; it is deeply rooted in
      <strong>brain chemistry</strong> and can be meaningfully influenced by diet, nutrients,
      and lifestyle.
    </p>
    <p>
      Neuronal signaling depends on electrolytes and ionic salts (sodium, potassium, magnesium,
      calcium) to generate action potentials and enable synaptic transmission. Neurotransmitters
      critical to memory, focus, motivation, and learning (acetylcholine, dopamine, glutamate)
      are synthesized and modulated by micronutrients and minerals. Thyroid hormones, which
      regulate brain metabolism and development, require iodine &mdash; historically delivered
      to populations through iodized salt.
    </p>
    <p>
      Iodine deficiency once caused widespread cretinism and severe intellectual impairment.
      The introduction of iodized salt produced measurable population-level gains in cognitive
      function, with studies showing average IQ improvements of approximately 13&ndash;15 points
      in previously deficient regions.
    </p>
    <p>
      Modern research confirms that diet and targeted nutrition directly affect executive
      function, memory consolidation, processing speed, and neuroplasticity. Optimized mineral
      balance, hydration, and specific nutrients &ldquo;groom&rdquo; and enhance intellectual
      performance, while deficiencies produce brain fog, reduced focus, and accelerated
      cognitive decline.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Intellect Salt</strong> is therefore more than a poetic name &mdash; it is a
      precise conceptual fit for the science of cognitive optimization: the right
      &ldquo;salts&rdquo; and foundational elements that enable the intellect to reach its
      highest expression.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- Why Premium -->
    <h2>Why This Domain Commands a Premium Acquisition Price</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>intellectsalt.com</strong> is not a commodity domain. It is a
      <strong>strategic brand asset</strong> with rare qualities that justify significant
      investment:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Multi-layered meaning</strong> &mdash; chemistry, philosophy (Emerson),
        cultural wit (&ldquo;salt&rdquo;), preservation, and modern cognitive science
        &mdash; giving it unusual depth and storytelling power.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Linguistic excellence</strong> &mdash; short, rhythmic, easy to spell and
        pronounce, yet sophisticated and ownable.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Category ownership</strong> &mdash; instantly positions any venture at the
        intersection of mind, science, and human potential.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Market timing</strong> &mdash; perfect for high-growth sectors: cognitive
        enhancement &amp; nootropics, AI + human intelligence, longevity &amp; brain health,
        EdTech, thought leadership platforms, neuroscience publishing, and premium wellness.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Development-ready</strong> &mdash; projects immediate credibility and
        substance. Ideal for product lines (e.g., electrolyte/nootropic formulations), media
        properties, SaaS tools, research institutes, or institutional brands.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Scarcity &amp; defensibility</strong> &mdash; a unique, evocative compound
        unlikely to be replicated or surpassed in resonance.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Premium domains offering this combination of memorability, authority, and cross-sector
      versatility routinely achieve strong acquisition prices when they deliver clear brand
      equity and long-term strategic value.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- Brand Applications -->
    <h2>Ideal Brand Applications</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Cognitive health, nootropics, or functional &ldquo;brain mineral&rdquo; formulations</li>
      <li>AI ethics, human-AI symbiosis, or intelligence augmentation platforms</li>
      <li>Lifelong learning, knowledge preservation, or executive education brands</li>
      <li>Neuroscience research, publishing, or thought leadership media</li>
      <li>High-performance consulting, philosophy of mind, or optimization communities</li>
      <li>Premium wellness or longevity brands focused on mental clarity and metabolic brain health</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <!-- The Opportunity -->
    <h2>The Opportunity</h2>
    <p>
      We live in an age of unprecedented cognitive demand, artificial intelligence, and intense
      focus on extending not just lifespan but <em>healthspan</em> and mental performance.
      <strong>intellectsalt.com</strong> offers immediate brand authority and a defensible
      position at the center of these conversations.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is the name for the venture that understands a profound truth: intellect is not merely
      acquired through information &mdash; it is enabled, preserved, and amplified by the right
      foundational elements. The right <em>salt</em>.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- Secure This Asset -->
    <h2>Secure This Asset</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>intellectsalt.com</strong> is available for acquisition by serious buyers and
      organizations seeking a distinctive, high-potential digital property.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Pricing available upon request (premium positioning)</li>
      <li>Flexible terms for qualified inquiries</li>
      <li>Optional branding strategy consultation available</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Ready to own the name that captures the essential seasoning of thought?</strong>
    </p>
    <p>Contact us today to discuss acquisition and next steps.</p>

    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <a
        href="mailto:sales@desertrich.com?subject=intellectsalt.com%20Acquisition%20Inquiry"
        class="cta-button text-lg"
      >
        Contact: sales@desertrich.com →
      </a>
    </div>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
